{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1809,"text":"The idea of eliminating poverty\nis a great goal."},{"time":7026,"text":"I don't think anyone\nin this room would disagree."},{"time":10512,"text":"What worries me\nis when politicians with money"},{"time":15060,"text":"and charismatic rock stars --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":17705,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":19309,"text":"use the words,"},{"time":20650,"text":"\" ... it all just sounds so, so simple.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":27073,"text":"Now, I've got no bucket of money today"},{"time":30189,"text":"and I've got no policy to release,"},{"time":33404,"text":"and I certainly haven't got a guitar."},{"time":35667,"text":"I'll leave that to others."},{"time":38440,"text":"But I do have an idea,"},{"time":40146,"text":"and that idea is called\nHousing for Health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43344,"text":"Housing for Health works with poor people."},{"time":46061,"text":"It works in the places where they live,"},{"time":49116,"text":"and the work is done\nto improve their health."},{"time":53049,"text":"Over the last 28 years,"},{"time":55228,"text":"this tough, grinding, dirty work"},{"time":58680,"text":"has been done by literally\nthousands of people around Australia"},{"time":63165,"text":"and, more recently, overseas,"},{"time":65629,"text":"and their work has proven"},{"time":67857,"text":"that focused design can improve\neven the poorest living environments."},{"time":73331,"text":"It can improve health"},{"time":74697,"text":"and it can play a part in reducing,\nif not eliminating, poverty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81256,"text":"I'm going to start\nwhere the story began --"},{"time":83331,"text":"1985, in Central Australia."},{"time":87200,"text":"A man called Yami Lester,\nan Aboriginal man,"},{"time":89947,"text":"was running a health service."},{"time":92625,"text":"Eighty percent of what walked\nin the door, in terms of illness,"},{"time":96599,"text":"was infectious disease --"},{"time":98812,"text":"third world, developing world\ninfectious disease,"},{"time":101684,"text":"caused by a poor living environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107381,"text":"Yami assembled a team in Alice Springs."},{"time":110977,"text":"He got a medical doctor."},{"time":113466,"text":"He got an environmental health guy."},{"time":116266,"text":"And he hand-selected a team\nof local Aboriginal people"},{"time":121034,"text":"to work on this project."},{"time":123540,"text":"Yami told us at that first meeting,"},{"time":125269,"text":"\"There's no money,\" --\nalways a good start --"},{"time":129035,"text":"\" ... no money, you have six months,"},{"time":132548,"text":"and I want you to start on a project --\"\nwhich, in his language,"},{"time":135586,"text":"he called \"Uwankara Palyanku Kanyintjaku,\""},{"time":138338,"text":"which, translated, is \"a plan\nto stop people getting sick\" --"},{"time":143324,"text":"a profound brief."},{"time":147265,"text":"That was our task."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150279,"text":"First step, the medical doctor went away\nfor about six months."},{"time":154932,"text":"And he worked on what were to become\nthese nine health goals --"},{"time":159387,"text":"what were we aiming at?"},{"time":163236,"text":"After six months of work,\nhe came to my office"},{"time":165451,"text":"and presented me with\nthose nine words on a piece of paper."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170046,"text":"[The 9 Healthy Living Practices: Washing,\nclothes, wastewater, nutrition, crowding,"},{"time":174066,"text":"animals, dust, temperature, injury]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":175757,"text":"I was very unimpressed.\nBig ideas need big words,"},{"time":179051,"text":"and preferably a lot of them."},{"time":181450,"text":"This didn't fit the bill."},{"time":183290,"text":"What I didn't see and what you can't see"},{"time":187680,"text":"was that he'd assembled thousands of pages"},{"time":192018,"text":"of local, national\nand international health research"},{"time":195808,"text":"that filled out the picture\nas to why these were the health targets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200634,"text":"The pictures that came a bit later\nhad a very simple reason."},{"time":204810,"text":"The Aboriginal people who were our bosses\nand the senior people"},{"time":208097,"text":"were most commonly illiterate,"},{"time":210463,"text":"so the story had to be told in pictures"},{"time":212646,"text":"of what these goals were."},{"time":214371,"text":"We worked with the community,"},{"time":216697,"text":"not telling them what was going to happen"},{"time":218704,"text":"in a language they didn't understand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221593,"text":"So we had the goals\nand each one of these goals --"},{"time":224860,"text":"and I won't go through them all --"},{"time":226745,"text":"puts at the center the person\nand their health issue,"},{"time":230848,"text":"and it then connects them"},{"time":232824,"text":"to the bits of the physical\nenvironment that are actually needed"},{"time":237333,"text":"to keep their health good."},{"time":239262,"text":"And the highest priority,\nyou see on the screen,"},{"time":241967,"text":"is washing people once a day,\nparticularly children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246310,"text":"And I hope most of you are thinking,"},{"time":248088,"text":"\"What? That sounds simple.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":249414,"text":"Now, I'm going to ask you all\na very personal question."},{"time":253494,"text":"This morning before you came,"},{"time":254899,"text":"who could have had a wash using a shower?"},{"time":260198,"text":"I'm not going to ask if you had a shower,\nbecause I'm too polite."},{"time":263437,"text":"That's it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264612,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":265637,"text":"All right, I think it's fair to say"},{"time":267423,"text":"most people here could have had\na shower this morning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270494,"text":"I'm going to ask you to do some more work."},{"time":272642,"text":"I want you all to select one of the houses"},{"time":275170,"text":"of the 25 houses you see on the screen."},{"time":277246,"text":"I want you to select one of them\nand note the position of that house"},{"time":280676,"text":"and keep that in your head."},{"time":282077,"text":"Have you all got a house?"},{"time":283627,"text":"I'm going to ask you to live there\nfor a few months,"},{"time":286101,"text":"so make sure you've got it right."},{"time":287731,"text":"It's in the northwest of\nWestern Australia, very pleasant place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290778,"text":"OK. Let's see if your shower\nin that house is working."},{"time":295328,"text":"I hear some \"Aw!\" and I hear some \"Ah!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":298487,"text":"If you get a green tick,\nyour shower's working."},{"time":301291,"text":"You and your kids are fine."},{"time":302601,"text":"If you get a red cross,"},{"time":304994,"text":"well, I've looked carefully\naround the room"},{"time":307257,"text":"and it's not going to make\nmuch difference to this crew."},{"time":310457,"text":"Why? Because you're all too old."},{"time":313005,"text":"I know that's going to come as a shock\nto some of you, but you are."},{"time":316241,"text":"And before you get offended and leave,"},{"time":318144,"text":"I've got to say that being too old,"},{"time":319984,"text":"in this case, means that pretty much\neveryone in the room, I think,"},{"time":323556,"text":"is over five years of age."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327465,"text":"We're really concerned\nwith kids naught to five."},{"time":330250,"text":"And why?"},{"time":331946,"text":"Washing is the antidote\nto the sort of bugs,"},{"time":336771,"text":"the common infectious diseases\nof the eyes, the ears,"},{"time":340018,"text":"the chest and the skin"},{"time":342438,"text":"that, if they occur in the first\nfive years of life,"},{"time":345334,"text":"permanently damage those organs."},{"time":349515,"text":"They leave a lifelong remnant."},{"time":353123,"text":"That means that by the age of five,"},{"time":355249,"text":"you can't see as well\nfor the rest of your life."},{"time":357559,"text":"You can't hear as well\nfor the rest of your life."},{"time":360073,"text":"You can't breathe as well."},{"time":361439,"text":"You've lost a third of your lung\ncapacity by the age of five."},{"time":364953,"text":"And even skin infection,"},{"time":366820,"text":"which we originally thought\nwasn't that big a problem,"},{"time":370400,"text":"mild skin infections\nnaught to five give you"},{"time":372649,"text":"a greatly increased\nchance of renal failure,"},{"time":375129,"text":"needing dialysis at age 40."},{"time":378364,"text":"This is a big deal, so the ticks\nand crosses on the screen"},{"time":381283,"text":"are actually critical for young kids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384697,"text":"Those ticks and crosses\nrepresent the 7,800 houses"},{"time":387830,"text":"we've looked at nationally\naround Australia,"},{"time":389918,"text":"the same proportion."},{"time":391351,"text":"What you see on the screen --"},{"time":392830,"text":"35 percent of those not-so-famous houses"},{"time":396087,"text":"lived in by 50,000 indigenous people --"},{"time":398987,"text":"35 percent had a working shower."},{"time":402167,"text":"Ten percent of those same 7,800 houses\nhad safe electrical systems."},{"time":408520,"text":"And 58 percent of those houses\nhad a working toilet."},{"time":415691,"text":"These are by a simple, standard test."},{"time":418457,"text":"In the case of the shower:"},{"time":420882,"text":"does it have hot and cold water,\ntwo taps that work,"},{"time":425414,"text":"a shower rose to get water\nonto your head or onto your body,"},{"time":430187,"text":"and a drain that takes the water away?"},{"time":432045,"text":"Not well-designed,\nnot beautiful, not elegant --"},{"time":436117,"text":"just that they function."},{"time":437308,"text":"And the same tests\nfor the electrical system"},{"time":439555,"text":"and the toilets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441811,"text":"Housing for Health projects\naren't about measuring failure --"},{"time":444767,"text":"they're actually about improving houses."},{"time":447475,"text":"We start on day one of every project."},{"time":451393,"text":"We've learned -- we don't make promises,\nwe don't do reports."},{"time":454656,"text":"We arrive in the morning with tools,\ntons of equipment, trades,"},{"time":460002,"text":"and we train up a local team\non the first day to start work."},{"time":463510,"text":"By the evening of the first day,"},{"time":465314,"text":"a few houses in that community are better\nthan when we started in the morning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469749,"text":"That work continues for six to 12 months,"},{"time":472028,"text":"until all the houses are improved"},{"time":473750,"text":"and we've spent our budget\nof 7,500 dollars total per house."},{"time":478375,"text":"That's our average budget."},{"time":480451,"text":"At the end of six months to a year,\nwe test every house again."},{"time":484771,"text":"It's very easy to spend money."},{"time":486856,"text":"It's very difficult to improve"},{"time":489198,"text":"the function of all those\nparts of the house."},{"time":491627,"text":"And for a whole house,\nthe nine healthy living practices,"},{"time":494647,"text":"we test, check and fix\n250 items in every house."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499161,"text":"And these are the results we can get\nwith our 7,500 dollars."},{"time":503275,"text":"We can get showers\nup to 86 percent working,"},{"time":505901,"text":"we can get electrical systems\nup to 77 percent working"},{"time":509716,"text":"and we can get 90 percent\nof toilets working"},{"time":512373,"text":"in those 7,500 houses."},{"time":515226,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":516431,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517703,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":524021,"text":"The teams do a great job,\nand that's their work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528816,"text":"I think there's an obvious question"},{"time":530956,"text":"that I hope you're thinking about."},{"time":533593,"text":"Why do we have to do this work?"},{"time":536059,"text":"Why are the houses in such poor condition?"},{"time":539271,"text":"Seventy percent of the work we do\nis due to lack of routine maintenance --"},{"time":542832,"text":"the sort of things that happen\nin all our houses."},{"time":545261,"text":"Things wear out, should have been done\nby state government or local government,"},{"time":549168,"text":"simply not done, the house doesn't work."},{"time":552378,"text":"Twenty-one percent of the things we fix\nare due to faulty construction --"},{"time":556293,"text":"literally things that are built\nupside down and back to front."},{"time":559318,"text":"They don't work, we have to fix them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562081,"text":"And if you've lived in Australia\nin the last 30 years, the final cause --"},{"time":567705,"text":"you will have heard always\nthat indigenous people trash houses."},{"time":571384,"text":"It's one of the almost\nrock-solid pieces of evidence"},{"time":574846,"text":"which I've never seen evidence for,"},{"time":576885,"text":"that's always reeled out as \"That's\nthe problem with indigenous housing.\""},{"time":580369,"text":"Well, nine percent\nof what we spend is damage,"},{"time":582563,"text":"misuse or abuse of any sort."},{"time":586120,"text":"We argue strongly that the people\nliving in the house"},{"time":589189,"text":"are simply not the problem."},{"time":591384,"text":"And we'll go a lot further than that;"},{"time":593206,"text":"the people living in the house\nare actually a major part of the solution."},{"time":597749,"text":"Seventy-five percent\nof our national team in Australia --"},{"time":601138,"text":"over 75 at the minute --"},{"time":603615,"text":"are actually local, indigenous people\nfrom the communities we work in."},{"time":607967,"text":"They do all aspects of the work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610192,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":615953,"text":"In 2010, for example, there were 831,"},{"time":619835,"text":"all over Australia,\nand the Torres Strait Islands,"},{"time":622432,"text":"all states, working to improve the houses\nwhere they and their families live,"},{"time":626915,"text":"and that's an important thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629198,"text":"Our work's always had a focus on health."},{"time":632332,"text":"That's the key."},{"time":634434,"text":"The developing world bug,\ntrachoma, causes blindness."},{"time":637918,"text":"It's a developing-world illness,"},{"time":640308,"text":"and yet, the picture you see behind"},{"time":642161,"text":"is in an Aboriginal community\nin the late 1990s,"},{"time":645981,"text":"where 95 percent of school-aged\nkids had active trachoma"},{"time":650005,"text":"in their eyes, doing damage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653142,"text":"OK, what do we do?"},{"time":654442,"text":"Well, first thing we do,\nwe get showers working."},{"time":657769,"text":"Why? Because that flushes the bug out."},{"time":659634,"text":"We put washing facilities\nin the school as well,"},{"time":661999,"text":"so kids can wash their faces\nmany times during the day."},{"time":664760,"text":"We wash the bug out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666673,"text":"Second, the eye doctors tell us\nthat dust scours the eye"},{"time":670538,"text":"and lets the bug in quick."},{"time":671879,"text":"So what do we do?"},{"time":673112,"text":"We call up the doctor of dust,\nand there is such a person."},{"time":676636,"text":"He was loaned to us by a mining company."},{"time":678586,"text":"He controls dust on mining company sites."},{"time":681280,"text":"And he came out and, within a day,"},{"time":683107,"text":"it worked out that most dust\nin this community"},{"time":685322,"text":"was within a meter of the ground,\nthe wind-driven dust --"},{"time":688596,"text":"so he suggested making mounds\nto catch the dust"},{"time":691501,"text":"before it went into the house area\nand affected the eyes of kids."},{"time":695247,"text":"So we used dirt to stop dust."},{"time":698814,"text":"We did it. He provided us dust monitors."},{"time":701606,"text":"We tested and we reduced the dust."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704086,"text":"Then we wanted to get rid\nof the bug generally."},{"time":706311,"text":"So how do we do that?"},{"time":707485,"text":"Well, we call up the doctor of flies --\nand, yes, there is a doctor of flies."},{"time":712728,"text":"As our Aboriginal mate said,"},{"time":714306,"text":"\"You white fellows ought to get out more.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":716441,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":718695,"text":"And the doctor of flies\nvery quickly determined"},{"time":721824,"text":"that there was one fly\nthat carried the bug."},{"time":725926,"text":"He could give school kids\nin this community"},{"time":728373,"text":"the beautiful fly trap you see\nabove in the slide."},{"time":731575,"text":"They could trap the flies,\nsend them to him in Perth."},{"time":734635,"text":"When the bug was in the gut,"},{"time":736112,"text":"he'd send back by return post\nsome dung beetles."},{"time":739103,"text":"The dung beetles ate the camel dung,"},{"time":741420,"text":"the flies died through lack of food,"},{"time":743190,"text":"and trachoma dropped."},{"time":744523,"text":"And over the year, trachoma dropped\nradically in this place, and stayed low."},{"time":750360,"text":"We changed the environment,\nnot just treated the eyes."},{"time":755079,"text":"And finally, you get a good eye."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758810,"text":"All these small health gains"},{"time":760729,"text":"and small pieces of the puzzle\nmake a big difference."},{"time":763975,"text":"The New South Wales Department of Health,"},{"time":765982,"text":"that radical organization,"},{"time":767283,"text":"did an independent trial over three years"},{"time":770847,"text":"to look at 10 years of the work\nwe've been doing"},{"time":773444,"text":"in these sorts of projects\nin New South Wales."},{"time":775936,"text":"And they found a 40 percent reduction\nin hospital admissions"},{"time":781504,"text":"for the illnesses that you could attribute\nto the poor environment --"},{"time":785258,"text":"a 40 percent reduction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":787652,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":795845,"text":"Just to show that the principles\nwe've used in Australia"},{"time":798591,"text":"can be used in other places,"},{"time":799953,"text":"I'm just going to go\nto one other place, and that's Nepal."},{"time":802715,"text":"And what a beautiful place to go."},{"time":804350,"text":"We were asked by a small\nvillage of 600 people"},{"time":807735,"text":"to go in and make toilets\nwhere none existed."},{"time":811764,"text":"Health was poor."},{"time":814270,"text":"We went in with no grand plan,"},{"time":815763,"text":"no grand promises of a great program,"},{"time":817914,"text":"just the offer to build\ntwo toilets for two families."},{"time":821146,"text":"It was during the design\nof the first toilet"},{"time":824518,"text":"that I went for lunch,"},{"time":825801,"text":"invited by the family\ninto their main room of the house."},{"time":828874,"text":"It was choking with smoke."},{"time":830898,"text":"People were cooking\non their only fuel source, green timber."},{"time":834497,"text":"The smoke coming off\nthat timber is choking,"},{"time":836618,"text":"and in an enclosed house,\nyou simply can't breathe."},{"time":840048,"text":"Later we found the leading cause\nof illness and death"},{"time":843962,"text":"in this particular region\nis through respiratory failure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847541,"text":"So all of a sudden, we had two problems."},{"time":849689,"text":"We were there originally\nto look at toilets"},{"time":851777,"text":"and get human waste\noff the ground, that's fine."},{"time":854099,"text":"But all of a sudden now\nthere was a second problem:"},{"time":857037,"text":"How do we actually get the smoke down?"},{"time":858886,"text":"So two problems, and design should\nbe about more than one thing."},{"time":862946,"text":"Solution: Take human waste,\ntake animal waste,"},{"time":866540,"text":"put it into a chamber,\nout of that, extract biogas,"},{"time":869922,"text":"methane gas."},{"time":871585,"text":"The gas gives three to four\nhours cooking a day --"},{"time":875010,"text":"clean, smokeless and free for the family."}]},{"cues":[{"time":878674,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":883842,"text":"I put it to you:\nis this eliminating poverty?"},{"time":886750,"text":"And the answer from the Nepali team\nwho's working at the minute would say,"},{"time":891186,"text":"don't be ridiculous --"},{"time":892361,"text":"we have three million\nmore toilets to build"},{"time":894457,"text":"before we can even make\na stab at that claim."},{"time":897332,"text":"And I don't pretend anything else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":900315,"text":"But as we all sit here today,"},{"time":902997,"text":"there are now over 100 toilets built"},{"time":904857,"text":"in this village and a couple nearby."},{"time":907294,"text":"Well over 1,000 people use those toilets."},{"time":910767,"text":"Yami Lama, he's a young boy."},{"time":913966,"text":"He's got significantly less gut infection\nbecause he's now got toilets,"},{"time":918294,"text":"and there isn't human waste on the ground."},{"time":922040,"text":"Kanji Maya, she's a mother,\nand a proud one."},{"time":925381,"text":"She's probably right now\ncooking lunch for her family"},{"time":929848,"text":"on biogas, smokeless fuel."},{"time":932317,"text":"Her lungs have got better,"},{"time":933587,"text":"and they'll get better as time increases,"},{"time":935587,"text":"because she's not cooking\nin the same smoke."},{"time":937792,"text":"Surya takes the waste\nout of the biogas chamber"},{"time":940418,"text":"when it's shed the gas,\nhe puts it on his crops."},{"time":943359,"text":"He's trebled his crop income,"},{"time":946081,"text":"more food for the family\nand more money for the family."},{"time":949020,"text":"And finally Bishnu,\nthe leader of the team,"},{"time":953798,"text":"has now understood that not only\nhave we built toilets,"},{"time":956985,"text":"we've also built a team,"},{"time":959161,"text":"and that team is now\nworking in two villages"},{"time":961817,"text":"where they're training up\nthe next two villages"},{"time":964314,"text":"to keep the work expanding."},{"time":966168,"text":"And that, to me, is the key."}]},{"cues":[{"time":967817,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":972508,"text":"People are not the problem."},{"time":976609,"text":"We've never found that."},{"time":978220,"text":"The problem: poor living environment,"},{"time":980939,"text":"poor housing and the bugs\nthat do people harm."},{"time":985137,"text":"None of those are limited by geography,\nby skin color or by religion."},{"time":990900,"text":"None of them."},{"time":993087,"text":"The common link between all\nthe work we've had to do"},{"time":995564,"text":"is one thing, and that's poverty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":999410,"text":"Nelson Mandela said, in the mid-2000s,\nnot too far from here,"},{"time":1003211,"text":"he said that like slavery and apartheid,\n\"Poverty is not natural."},{"time":1009516,"text":"It is man-made and can be\novercome and eradicated"},{"time":1013399,"text":"by the actions of human beings.\""},{"time":1016864,"text":"I want to end by saying"},{"time":1018197,"text":"it's been the actions of thousands\nof ordinary human beings"},{"time":1024378,"text":"doing -- I think -- extraordinary work,"},{"time":1027627,"text":"that have actually improved health,"},{"time":1030295,"text":"and, maybe only in a small way,\nreduced poverty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1033440,"text":"Thank you very much for your time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1035136,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}